{
  "texts": [
    "The pupils were equal, round, and reactive to light without a relative afferent pupillary defect.",
    "IOP was 12 on the right and 14 on the left.",
    "Slit lamp examination was normal other than early nuclear sclerosis.",
    "Dilated posterior segment evaluation demonstrated pigment mottling of the superior macula on the right but was otherwise unremarkable.",
    "Ocular motility examination revealed a -2 abduction deficit on the right with an esotropia of 25 prism diopters in the right gaze, 10 prism diopters in the primary gaze, and 2 prism diopters in the left gaze."
  ]
}